{"lemma":"مِسْعَرٌ","slug":"مِسْعَرٌ","root":"س.ع.ر","root_slug":"س-ع-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ع-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19820"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19820","headword_ar":"مِسْعَرٌ","root":"sEr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoEaArN","text_ar":"مِسْعَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"instrument of iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which a fire is stirred"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made to burn"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burn up"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (S, * K, * TA:) pl. (of the former, A)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAEiru","text_ar":"مَسَاعِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA) and [of the latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAEiyru","text_ar":"مَسَاعِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence one says of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lamisoEaru HarobK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَمِسْعَرُ حَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one who makes the fire of war to rage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stirrer of the fire of war."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also the former, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoEarN","text_ar":"مِسْعَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Long;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, K;) applied to a neck (K) or some other thing: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, K.) ―         -b4-  And, applied to a dog, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mad."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 785.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEirN","text_ar":"سَعِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmisoEaru","text_ar":"المِسْعَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to a horse means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aal~a*iY yuTiyHu qawaAy^imahu mutafar~iqapN walaA Dabora lahu","text_ar":"اَلَّذِى يُطِيحُ قَوَايِمَهُ مُتَفَرِّقَةٌ وَلَا ضَبْرَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That makes his legs to fall spread apart, and that has no leaping with his legs put together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or, in the words of AO, [and so in the O,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*Y tuTiyHu qawaAy^imahu","text_ar":"الذى تُطِيحُ قَوَايِمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose legs thow makest to fall"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (TA:) [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wlA Sabora lahu","text_ar":"ولا صَبْرَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is, I doubt not, a mistake: and in the TA is added,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqyl wavobN mujotamiEu AlqawaAy^imi","text_ar":"وقيل وَثْبٌ مُجْتَمِعُ القَوَايِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqyl","text_ar":"وقيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is evidently a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wahuwa","text_ar":"وَهُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", referring to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dabor","text_ar":"ضَبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is well known as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wavobN","text_ar":"وَثْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujotamiEu AlqawaAy^imi","text_ar":"مُجْتَمِعُ القَوَايِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaAEirN","text_ar":"مُسَاعِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (AO.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}